      • onSleepProgressDetail

        void onSleepProgressDetail(java.lang.String day,
                           int packagenumber)
        Returns the details of reading sleep. This interface is only used for testing, so developers can check the reading progress.
        parameters:
        day - indicates that the data of the day is being read, the data of three days a day, the order of reading is today-yesterday-the day before yesterday
        packagenumber - indicates the number of packets. The data return for a day starts with the largest packet and decreases in order.
